<p>Making a new game.</p>

<h3 id="how-did-i-get-into-new-game">How Did I get Into New Game?</h3>
<p>I got into New Game because one of my close friends of mine who doesnâ€™t watch anime, but is into programming, reccomended the anime to me. He knew I just got into anime a few months ago, and I wanted to watch a bunch of short animes first to see what genres I like and dislike. Furthermore, I decided to try it because I too want to become a programmer, and I wanted to see what kind of anime he watched as his first anime (It was quite different from my first anime, Attack On Titan to say the least).</p>

<h3 id="synopsis">Synopsis</h3>
<p>Suzukaze Aoba just graduated high school and got a job as one of the artists as Eagle Jump, and joins the character team there. Aoba is met by a lot of friendly and welcoming people at Eagle Jump. She realizes that her boss is the character designer of her favourite game when she was a child, Fairies Story and Fairies Story II. Late that night, it gets revealed to Aoba that the next game they are making is Fairies Story III. How will Fairies Story III turn out? What other games will Aoba and the Eagle Jump company decide to make in the future?</p>

<h3 id="any-flawsdislikes">Any Flaws/Dislikes?</h3>
<p>Some things that I disliked from the anime is that I got to experience some things I did not get to experience during Promised Neverland and Attack On Titan. I got to (unfortunately) experience anime girls in underwear, showering, changing, and literally naked. These kind of made me uncomfortable, since I prefer my anime characters to be fully clothed. There are some parts that they sexualized that I didnâ€™t really like, like a zoom in pan of someones butt or underwear. <br /><br /></p>

<p>One thing I love in either a game, book, or anime is a huge and complicated story, and there isnâ€™t very much of a story in this anime. The main story is the progress made for Fariy Story III and other games theyâ€™ve created in season 2 of the anime. The end goal of the anime was essentially to finish a game within the timespan, and other little side story stuff, instead of killing beasts in order to save the world. <br /><br /></p>

<p>I also feel like they couldâ€™ve streteched some parts out of the story, with the main one being:</p>
<details>
  <summary>Spoilers For S2</summary>
In season 2, there was a meeting between Yagami, Aoba, Hazuki, Christina, Rin, and Umiko. Christina and Hazuki told Aoba that she couldn't make the key visuals, even though she was the main chracter designer and Yagami should do it instead  because Yagami's name will bring more revenue and she is more experienced. Firstly, this was one of the first times they brought up the money/profit aspect FOR THE GAME in the story. I'm not sure if it's just me, but I feel like Hazuki and Christina were being too harsh on Aoba even thought she only has 1 year of art experience. Rin also agreed with Hazuki and Christina, which I find kind of weird since I felt like Rin would be the one supporting Aoba. Some things they said to Aoba were: <br /><br />
"If you don't do it Yagami, we'll hire a professional" <br /><br />
"You don't stand a chance against Yagami's 8 year experience"<br /><br />
"It's a fixed result you know Aoba, no matter how good your art piece is, we're going to use Yagami's artwork for the brand name which'll lead to more sales"  <br /><br />

I'm pretty sure you're not supposed to say this to someone who is in their first year of art experience, it could break their confidence. Furthermore, how do you get experience and get your name out there if you can't do things that'll get out more experience. Also, Aoba's dream is to be like Yagami, and I feel like in a way, Hazuki and Christina is preventing that. Typically, I wouldn't be defending a main character this much because they have to get ragged on for the story, but Aoba is too nice and pure of a person to get ragged on. One thing I found crazy was that Aoba just shrug it off like it was nothing, and there was no sense of tension between any of them. <br /><br />

Aoba and Yagami did the competetion to see who gets the key visuals, and obviously Yagami won. They didn't even show the competition like the first competetion for the character designer. One thing I wished was that this would've been more then one episode, not even, like 10 minutes of an episode.I feel like they could've expanded on it more just like the first competition.  

</details>

<h3 id="characters">Characters</h3>
<p>The characters are all either very cutesy or very socially awkward. Not going to lie, this is what I thought what anime wold be, very cutesy artwork with not much of a story, and a very cutesy or socially awkward personailty. My favourite character, like most people in the anime, is Hifumi Tamimoto. Sheâ€™s very shy, socially awakard, and really pretty too, with her blue sparkling eyes. 
