<h3 id="music">Music</h3>
<p>As for the music, the season 1 opening was pretty decent, it was cutesy and it showâ€™s everyoneâ€™s personality at the company very effectively in a short period of time. Not going to lie, the anime opening felt pretty long, being 1:30. However, Attack On Titans were either the same or longer, so I guess the New Game intro didnâ€™t hook me in that much <a href="ttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XvWD1Cqx4X8">Season 1 Opening</a>. As season 2 intro, I really enjoyed it, especially the chorus. The chrous is really really catchy. Out of all the music played in New Game, the season 2 intro is my favourite <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ee439rxfiaM">Season 2 Opening</a>. For the season 2 intro, 0:47 is very much waifu materialâ€¦ <a href="https://youtu.be/Ee439rxfiaM?t=47">Season 2 Waifu Material</a> <br /><br /></p>

<p>Season 1 and 2 both have the same outro song. The outro was decent, with the chorus being pretty catchy. As for the animation, it seemed like they were in a video game world simulation that they programmed and made art for, which I thought was pretty neat. <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_8GQagRv8F8">Season 1 &amp; 2 Outro</a></p>

<h3 id="final-thoughts-and-grade">Final Thoughts and Grade</h3>
<p>This anime was deinfetly a different vibe and genre from the action and deep story of Attack on Titan and Promised Neverland. Nevertheless, I still relatively enjoyed the story, characters, and music, since I would like to be apart of a programming company sometime in the future after university. It is confirmed that there will be a New Game season 3 coming out sometime in the summer of 2022, and I will update this blog when it happens. As for now, I would have to rate New Game! a 7.5/10 due to the lack of story, some uncomfortable scenes, medoicre intro, and great cutesy and relatable characters.</p>
